rende sowie praktisch und forschend tätige Personen finden hier leichten Zugang zur Wissenschaftsdidaktik und ihren innovativen Erkenntnispotentialen.  afunded by Open-Access-Fonds der Universität Hamburg  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBildung. 4aBildungsforschung. 4aBildungssoziologie. 4aEmpirie. 4aExperiment. 4aFachdidaktik. 4aForschung. 4aHermeneutik. 4aMethodologie. 4aPraxis. 4aPädagogik. 4aReflexion. 4aTheorie. 4aUniversität. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftsdidaktik. 4aWissenschaftssoziologie. 7aEDUCATION / Organizations & Institutions.2bisacsh  aEducation.  aEducational Research.  aEmpirical Research.  aExperiment.  aHermeneutics.  aMethodology.  aPedagogy.  aPractice.  aResearch.  aScience Didactics.  aScience.  aSociology of Education.  aSociology of Science.  aSubject Didactics.  aTheory.  aUniversity.1 aBalzer, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellmann, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerk, Ivo van den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBohndick, Carla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoriand, Rotraud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFahr, Uwe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofhues, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKollmer, Imke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKönig, Hannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangemeyer, Ines, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/